Uncovering Secrets: A Deep Dive into the Dev Diaries TryHackMe Room
Author: Abouhafs Fatima Zahra
Date: July 2026
In the world of cybersecurity, a common misconception is that deleting files from a repository effectively removes them from existence. As we explore the Dev Diaries room on TryHackMe, we peel back the layers of Open Source Intelligence (OSINT) and version control security to demonstrate why Git history is a treasure trove for threat actors.
This walkthrough outlines the investigative process used to uncover sensitive information and hidden flags within a misconfigured development environment.

